[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating Javac13Test needs**\n\nI need to add a dedicated test, Javac13Test, outside library packages. The existing ant.ant package is okay, but I have to use the public API without direct reflection. It's crucial to ensure that Javac13 can execute reflection. The issue is that Ant 1.6 looks for `com.sun.tools.javac.Main compile(String[])`, but I wonder if this class exists in JDK 21. It seems the `Main` class in `jdk.compiler` is public with a no-arg constructor and an integer return type for its compile method. However, I’m questioning module access and whether the native image can include Java compiler classes.\n\n**Configuring Javac13 tests**\n\nI need to be cautious because the Ant code may already have reachability, but I'm not entirely sure. I should write a test that executes `Javac13.execute`. This requires me to properly configure the Javac task. I might find the right context for the source in some upstream tests. So, I’ll start by searching for existing tests related to `Javac13` to see how they set things up. It’s important to get this right!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_089492658642b3cd0169efed9083248190a9dfd7a8f3a7ef54\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp7-2ZxjThAGMF1bLuMd0iCwwBM_R0VCCQok3qNVeIRbxZmw5vNMvxR3oE64ja4GVxUtrgNRPWiOY7lnCe0u9Vfo_Hh8z2h9OoTUoE72okYJzcOZch6zAOj1NxwmNIuIjaQQdoM6DM8DEbXZd2GsvuDqX4WgWqwR95W_TdnWYFO83TjaNfj-44FAU_6gYQ5u6t-BJfznAtkNb1Y0XR_qqH4hJK_VaP1LSA4gugVhjsF9Yn0MKRab4FFt-OaBhjLBwsb3baSaiVfoZ-iyY5eofE0Ughx5LOWBCOna_6mVT0qhGhWSqF9l4oH6c0PPPbnyzaHULeKGrJYUDdyJRGMFNaHfI7igsXfP-_OqLN9vTTJ_vw9z2WIRTvStJfOgjvi3ttfn8yOrMTBjlfX0sZZAqsFk3-PIdMei7pb_zs8YT2O1SxooHYxvteTcAVi2HF6-B-zTBQAvYvw86knzv2BY24ZEIbMQj_K_w1XkLxHShDGOYwstMv-gDkRHEw6EqiFNMNiMLmr1h2KRhESmqget96ct7Na44Ep-nzeOTAa_flf7HNirTffjfsWPKAoqJ9_a5XbgJGWfW9e-b6B49aYHP1gv290r8zIX-Fj44K_eOtEtz35i4ny1-INlQawuNXHewAoy0a4Rpm1QKrxDke0iJBsILx6vxSB0HJ